race.comment: Tricky little sprint to open proceedings. GRACIE'S RAIN (2) is going well for this. She found 1200m at Listed level too tough at Geelong two back but was very good last time behind Gallant Son who is being kept very safe in the Oakleigh Plate later. She didn't get things to suit there either and the wide draw here should be fine - she can cross and lead and take catching. CASTELLAR (4) also brings Gallant Son form having placed behind him fresh at Flemington. He won well here last time over 1000m and can measure up to this. EXPULSION (12) is going well, far too good fresh, sticking on well for third here last time. She can continue to improve. ALONG THE RIVER (8) is flying without winning. Fancy he needs to drop back to 1000m but he'll run another strong race.
